720854f-a.text:
225-to 239 Lenox Ave., west side, north from West 121st to 122nd Streets. Also shown is West 12lst Street, at, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Lenox Ave. The Congregation Chevrah Son of Israel occupy the corner building that bears No. 225 Lenox Ave. The two adjoining buildings, Nos. 227 and 229 were formerly known as Lenox Hall and
Savigny Hall, respectively.
July 28, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
